    "summary": "SQL injection vector using null byte for PDO\nThe PDO adapters of Zend Framework 1 do not filter null bytes values in SQL statements. A PDO adapter can treat null bytes in a query as a string terminator, allowing an attacker to add arbitrary SQL following a null byte, and thus create a SQL injection. This only impacts MsSql and SQLite adapters.",
